💡 Pro Tips for CML-Free 

Save snapshots after each phase config — CML lets you save/restore node states 

Use Unmanaged Switches (unlimited, free) as a central hub to connect all nodes physically without wasting node slots 

Alpine Linux hosts are very lightweight (use those over Ubuntu to save RAM) 

Label your nodes clearly in the canvas — CML supports annotations 

Export your lab as a YAML file after each phase to back up your work 

 
